  "prompt": "Will the other US cellular carriers follow T-Mobile's lead and provide free data for streaming music?",
  "response": "While I cannot predict the future, it is possible that other US cellular carriers may consider following T-Mobile's lead in offering free data for streaming music. T-Mobile has been known for its competitive strategies, and when they implement popular features, other carriers often respond to stay competitive.\n\nHowever, whether other carriers will adopt similar policies depends on several factors, including market competition, consumer demand, and their own business strategies. If T-Mobile's initiative proves to be successful and popular among customers, it's likely that other carriers will evaluate the potential benefits of offering comparable options.\n\nIt's always a good idea to keep an eye on announcements from major carriers, as they regularly update their plans and promotional offerings based on market trends and customer preferences.",
